               <msContents>
                  <summary> An incomplete, anonymous work entitled <title>Ansāb-i Afghānān</title>
                     (Genealogies of the Afghans), concerning the history of Afghan tribes,
                     especially the Rohillas. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_442-item1">
                     <author key="person_f407">
                        <persName xml:lang="en" type="anonymous" role="abr">Anonymous</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7237">Ansāb-i Afghānān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7237">انساب افغانان</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> آغاز انساب افغانان و کیفیت و ماهیت سلسله ایشان و آنچه که
                        مردم هند ایشانرا روهلها میگویند این نسبت روهله چیست. </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="40b" to="40b"> برگ ۴۰پ (folio
                           40b):</locus> تا کی رد خواب غفلت باشی ای دون و ما خلت الجن والانسن الا
                        لیعبدون ربنا الهدنا الصراط المستقیم. </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon.</colophon>
                     <note>The author states on the final folio that he culled information from
                        various sources, including the <title>Khulaṣat al-Ānsāb</title> by <persName
                           role="ant" key="person_63646020" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/63646020/"
                           >Ḥāfiẓ Raḥmat Khān (ca. 1710–1774)</persName>, the <title>Tārīkh-i
                           Shīrshāh</title> by <persName role="ant" key="person_11930225"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/11930225/">ʻAbbās Khān Sarvānī (fl.
                           1579)</persName>, the <title>Khulāṣat al-Tavārīkh</title> by <persName
                           role="ant" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/28973620/" key="person_28973620"
                           >Sūjan Rāʼi (fl. 1690–1698)</persName>, the <title>Tārīkh-i
                           Firishtah</title> by <persName key="person_95224795"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/95224795">Muḥammad Qāsim Hindū Shāh Astarābādī
                           (d. ca. 1620) </persName>, known as '<addName key="person_95224795"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/95224795" type="penname">Firishtah</addName>'
                        (see Rylands <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6876"><idno>Persian
                              MS 378</idno></ref> to 380 and 826) and the <title>Zubdat
                           al-Tavārīkh</title> by <persName role="ant"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/4163208250607231592/"
                           key="person_4163208250607231592">Nūr al-Ḥaqq Dihlavī (d.
                           1662–1663</persName>, see Rylands <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6883"><idno>Persian
                              MS 384</idno></ref>). The author also references the <title>Majma'
                           al-Tavārīkh</title>, probably that of <persName cert="medium" role="ant"
                           key="person_5163208231807231310"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/5163208231807231310">Ḥaydar ibn ʻAlī Ḥusaynī
                           Rāzī (fl. 1611–1619)</persName>, as well as the <title>Ḥadīqat
                           al-Aqālīm</title> completed by <persName role="ant"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/297981831/" key="person_297981831">Murtaz̤ā
                           Ḥusayn Bilgrāmī (ca. 1720–1790)</persName> sometime between <date
                           cert="medium" calendar="#Gregorian" from="1775" to="1781">1775 to
                           1781</date> (see Rylands <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7193"><idno>Persian
                              MS 69</idno></ref>). Therefore, this work must date subsequent to the
                        last title. </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
